external_knowledge:
- 'trees in the forest' refers to employees in the department;
- 'overseen by John Doe' means the department managed by the user named 'John Doe';
- 'measured from the ground to the sky' refers to the height of the employees in inches;
- 'during the year of the great growth' refers to the period between January 1, 2022, and December 31, 2022.

- "stands out above the crowd" refers to the average salary being higher than the average salary of all employees in the same department;
- "like a lighthouse in the night" is a metaphor for being significantly higher or more prominent;
- "from the highest to the lowest" means the results are ordered by average salary in descending order.

- 'Shining stars' refers to employees with a high rating (rating >= 4) in performance evaluations;
- 'Sacred scrolls of sensitive data' refers to records accessed with the 'view' type in the access logs;
- The query limits the results to the top 10 employees.
